{
  "analysis": "We are in /app as root. We need to install and run Windows XP SP3 in QEMU, with disk image at /app/isos/xp.img and ISO at /app/isos/xp.iso. We also need to configure QEMU's VNC on display :1 (port 5901), and set up a web interface (nginx on port 80) so remote users can monitor, ideally using noVNC via websockify. Additionally, the admin account should be named tb-admin, and we have an API at /app/read_xp_key_from_cdrom_box to fetch the product key. Installing Windows XP typically requires interactive steps; to automate, we can provide an unattended setup answer file (WINNT.SIF) via a QEMU floppy image, including ProductKey and commands to create a tb-admin account with administrator privileges during GuiRunOnce. We will install necessary packages (qemu-system-i386, qemu-utils, nginx, novnc, websockify, dosfstools, mtools), create the qcow2 disk, craft a FAT-formatted floppy image with WINNT.SIF using the OCR key, configure nginx to serve noVNC and proxy websocket traffic to websockify, start websockify, and launch QEMU in the background with VNC exposed on 0.0.0.0:5901 and the floppy attached for unattended install. We will verify listening ports. The VM will be installing; reaching the login screen will take time but the setup should proceed unattended.",
  "plan": "1) Verify the XP ISO exists. 2) Create the qcow2 disk image /app/isos/xp.img (20G). 3) Install required packages: QEMU, utilities, nginx, novnc, websockify, and tools to build a FAT floppy image. 4) Build a 1.44MB FAT floppy image and mount it. 5) Retrieve the Windows XP product key via /app/read_xp_key_from_cdrom_box and write WINNT.SIF with FullUnattended settings, NTFS formatting, auto-partitioning, and GuiRunOnce commands to create a tb-admin account and add it to Administrators. 6) Unmount the floppy image. 7) Configure nginx to serve /usr/share/novnc and proxy /websockify to localhost:6080. 8) Start/restart nginx. 9) Start websockify to connect browser websockets to QEMU's VNC on 5901. 10) Launch the QEMU VM with -vnc 0.0.0.0:1, attach the cdrom and floppy, boot from cd, and run installation unattended, leaving it running in background. 11) Verify that ports 80, 6080, and 5901 are listening. Expectation: QEMU will begin installation, exposed via VNC and web interface; after unattended setup completes, the system should reach the Windows XP login screen with tb-admin created.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -l /app/isos/xp.iso
",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "qemu-img create -f qcow2 /app/isos/xp.img 20G
",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-get update
",
      "duration": 20.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-get install -y qemu-system-x86 qemu-utils nginx novnc websockify dosfstools mtools
",
      "duration": 40.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "dd if=/dev/zero of=/app/isos/xp_unattend.vfd bs=1024 count=1440
",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkfs.vfat -n XPUNATT /app/isos/xp_unattend.vfd
",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /mnt/floppy
",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mount -o loop /app/isos/xp_unattend.vfd /mnt/floppy
",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "XPKEY=$(/app/read_xp_key_from_cdrom_box)
",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /mnt/floppy/WINNT.SIF <<EOF
[Data]
AutoPartition=1
MsDosInitiated="0"
UnattendedInstall="Yes"

[Unattended]
UnattendMode=FullUnattended
OemSkipEula=Yes
FileSystem=NTFS
Repartition=Yes
TargetPath=\WINDOWS
WaitForReboot=No

[GuiUnattended]
AdminPassword=*
EncryptedAdminPassword=No
TimeZone=035
OEMSkipRegional=1
OemSkipWelcome=1

[UserData]
ProductKey=$XPKEY
FullName="tb-admin"
OrgName="tb-admin"
ComputerName=XPVM

[Display]
BitsPerPel=32
XResolution=1024
YResolution=768
VRefresh=60

[Identification]
JoinWorkgroup=WORKGROUP

[Networking]
InstallDefaultComponents=Yes

[Components]
msmsgs=off
zonegames=off

[Shell]
DefaultStartPanelOff=Yes

[GuiRunOnce]
Command0=cmd /c net user tb-admin /add
Command1=cmd /c net localgroup administrators tb-admin /add
EOF
",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sync
",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "umount /mnt/floppy
",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /etc/nginx/sites-available/novnc <<'EOF'
server {
    listen 80 default_server;
    server_name _;
    root /usr/share/novnc;
    index vnc.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /vnc.html;
    }

    location /websockify {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:6080;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
        proxy_read_timeout 86400;
    }
}
EOF
",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ln -sf /etc/nginx/sites-available/novnc /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/novnc
",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "rm -f /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default
",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nginx -t
",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "systemctl restart nginx || service nginx restart || true
",
      "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup websockify 0.0.0.0:6080 127.0.0.1:5901 >/app/websockify.log 2>&1 &
",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup qemu-system-i386 -m 1024 -smp 1 -cpu pentium3 -drive file=/app/isos/xp.img,format=qcow2,if=ide,index=0 -cdrom /app/isos/xp.iso -boot d -fda /app/isos/xp_unattend.vfd -vnc 0.0.0.0:1 -k en-us -rtc base=localtime -name "Windows XP SP3" >/app/qemu-xp.log 2>&1 &
",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ss -ltnp | grep -E '(:80|:6080|:5901)'
",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

